{"title": "SIA, Scoot offering over 420,000 discounted tickets from Oct 25", "tags": "singapore", "timestamp": "2024-10-09", "content": "SINGAPORE - Snap up wallet-friendly tickets from Singapore Airlines (SIA) and its budget carrier Scoot for your next holiday to Europe and Asia from Oct 25.\nMore than 420,000 discounted tickets will be available online and at a three-day fair in Suntec City, the airlines said on Oct 9 in a joint statement about their largest travel fair.\nThe discounts will apply to selected Scoot flights from November 2024 to October 2025, as well as SIA flights from January to September 2025.\nAmong discounted tickets offered by SIA from Singapore to 78 global destinations are the airline\u2019s new destinations of Brussels and London Gatwick Airport, as well as upcoming services to Beijing Daxing International Airport.\nMore than 200,000 business class, premium economy class and economy class round-trip tickets will be up for grabs from the flagship carrier.\nScoot\u2019s discounts will cover flights across the Asia-Pacific region and Europe, and include the new destinations of Kertajati in Indonesia, Koh Samui in Thailand, and Melaka in Malaysia.\nThis will apply to 220,000 one-way economy and ScootPlus tickets to 57 destinations, including China, Japan and South Korea, across its network.\nAirfares will start from as low as $71, said Scoot in a separate statement.\nOnline sales will run until Nov 7 on SIA and Scoot\u2019s websites and mobile applications, and through their appointed travel agents.\nThe physical three-day fair will be held from Oct 25 to 27 at Suntec Singapore Convention and Exhibition Centre\u2019s halls 401 and 402, featuring the discounted tickets and exclusive travel deals from participating travel agents and partners.\nVisitors to the fair can participate in a lucky draw for three pairs of SIA business class round-trip tickets, with hotel accommodation, to Hong Kong, Shanghai and Istanbul.\nOther prizes include round-trip SIA business class tickets with hotel stays in Bangkok, Phuket and Male, as well as Scoot vouchers worth up to $5,000.\nMeanwhile, the top spender on the airlines\u2019 lifestyle rewards app Kris+ will win a four-day, three-night trip to the Maldives.\nKrisShop will offer new merchandise for sale, including limited-edition figurines featuring a \u201cnew mystery character\u201d."}